Brutas, sorry I missed your post somehow. I think you have made an interesting point. I would like to add that there are 3 types of relationships you have included in your post. 1) Logical relationships: If A = B and B = C, then A = C; 2) Physical relationships: A bumps into B; 3) Pyschological relationships: A loves B. Some argue that 2 and 3 really are the same. At any rate, *relationships* come to play in Metaphysics when talking about 1 and 2 above, and I think rarely 3. If A loves B, then there is no question that A has some sort of logical or physical relationship with B. Now which is more important than the other? I think that 3 wins hands down. I could really care less if the world is another's dream (an illusion), or the figment of my imagination (Solipsism) or ultimately physical. To me emotion is very powerful and is what counts day to day. When I die I will not be asking if the world is real. I will be asking for those people I love be they imaginary or real. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>
