: Powerful statement</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;My take of what you said: existence is based on a union of 'something' or 'SUMthing' and this union creates being,existence,life(whatever its called).&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What am I saying about &quot;existence&quot;? Not much really. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Let me seperate out two ideas I have and please knock them around a bit. There is no such thing as &quot;Existence&quot; in and of itself. There are worlds that contain things (like you and I) and one of those worlds is the *actual* world (btw, a &quot;world&quot; is simply a collection) and all the rest of them are &quot;possible worlds&quot;. What is actual is what is real and what exists. The actual world is that which contains instances of logically possible concepts. For example, the actual world doesn't contain an instance of a &quot;round-square&quot; because that is not possible; in fact, &quot;round-squares&quot; are not even real. However, the concept &quot;human being&quot; does have instances. Human beings are both real and exist. That is to say the concept is coherent and there is an instance of it. Let me toss this out while I am here.... The concept of &quot;Sherlock Holmes&quot; is coherent. So, Sherlock is real, but does he exist? As far as we know there are no instances of the concept anywhere, so the easy answer is he does not exist.<br>
<br>
Concerning the remainder of your post, you have some well thought out ideas. I agree that passion must walk alongside the dryness of truth. I also agree that when one attempts to lose emotional content (what you refer to as &quot;spirituality&quot;) they have lost out. At the end of reason are two types of people, in my opinion: 1) dead ones 2) living one. Those who keep passion in their lives are alive.<br>
<br>
I will not leave aside what you are writing about &quot;perfection&quot; until you can elaborate more on the topic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>
