<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;IMO perfection(the way we view it) happens in its physical sense. It just happens on such a miniscule scale of time that we don't notice it.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Perfection in its &quot;physical sense&quot; as opposed to another sense of the word? I understand to some extent what you are saying about the harmony of the blinkers in your example so let me respond there.<br>
<br>
I think you may be saying something like the blinkers share a property of &quot;harmonius blinking&quot; for a short duration of time. The property of blinking in harmony is a example of what &quot;perfection&quot; means. Something like that?<br>
<br>
If so, then time may be extraneous to your claim. Further, you would be in good company with Platonists through the ages who believe there are things that exist called &quot;universals&quot; (Plato calls them &quot;Idea Forms&quot;). The Platonist view of Universals is that shared properties of a class are the expression of a form. For example, if you have Red hair and I have Red hair the shared property of &quot;Redness&quot; is the expression of the form &quot;Red&quot;. It is Plato's &quot;Idea Forms&quot; that evolves into the ideas of &quot;perfection&quot;. If I have &quot;red&quot; hair and you have &quot;red&quot; hair, then there must be an ideal color of &quot;red&quot;, some think.<br>
<br>
Suffice it to say there are numerous problems with that view (imo). One large problem deal with how we could possibly know what the Idea Form &quot;red&quot; is. A deeper issue is what should the scale look like with Idea Red at the top and what at the bottom and in between? Lastly, how would we overcome perceptions of red (for example) to determine the Idea Form of Red? How I see &quot;red&quot; will differ from how you see that color. If Quantum Mechanics has shown anything at all it has demonstrated the realitivity of measurement. How we measure properties (like &quot;red) is contingent upon our physical construction. O.k., this post is too long now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>
