Really? That is news to me. What contemporary Roman texts refer to Jesus? BTW, if you are going to quote the piece from Flavius Josephus there are two problems you will need to overcome: 1) Josephus is not contemporary to Jesus; 2) most biblical scholars agree that the piece is a forgery. However, if you have some new information I would truly be interested. :P<br>
